<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,778,1928]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,550,778,804]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Localities in the Indian Ocean</emphasis>
. Widespread along the African East Coast. McKenzie Point, 
<collectingCountry box="[1320,1436,778,804]" name="Kenya" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Mombasa</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[159,241,818,844]" name="Kenya" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Kenya</collectingCountry>
), small algae from a rocky tide pool at the fence of the Four Seasons Restaurant (
<date box="[1222,1358,818,844]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1991-10-10">
<number box="[1222,1251,818,844]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="10.0">10</number>
/ 
<number box="[1261,1290,818,844]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="10.0">10</number>
/ 
<number box="[1299,1358,818,844]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</date>
) (
<typeStatus box="[1384,1436,818,844]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
locality). Same locality, at the mouth of Tudor Creek, on 
<taxonomicName box="[814,1062,858,883]" class="Liliopsida" family="Hydrocharitaceae" genus="Thalassia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alismatales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hemprichii">
<emphasis box="[814,1062,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Thalassia hemprichii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, covered by the epiphyte 
<taxonomicName class="Ulvophyceae" family="Ulvaceae" genus="Enteromorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ulvales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="kylinii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Enteromorpha kylinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
